cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with information transmission over a noisy channel and proposes a method for shaping the constellation to improve energy efficiency. 
2. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper is focused on improving the performance of a communication system using LDPC coding and APSK modulation. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of iterative decoding and shaping to improve the performance of a communication system, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a system for shaping the constellation and optimizing the degree distribution of the LDPC code, which can be considered a control system. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the transmission of multimedia data using LDPC coding and APSK modulation, which is relevant to the multimedia field.
